.TH "tipc_setsockopt" 9 "tipc_setsockopt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tipc_setsockopt \- set socket option
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tipc_setsockopt
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "int lvl "  ","
.BI "int opt "  ","
.BI "sockptr_t ov "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket structure
.IP "lvl" 12
option level
.IP "opt" 12
option identifier
.IP "ov" 12
pointer to new option value
.IP "ol" 12
length of option value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For stream sockets only, accepts and ignores all IPPROTO_TCP options
(to ease compatibility).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, errno otherwise
